The paper proposes a novel algorithm for learning context-specific registration metrics, which involves optimizing a non-convex function using the concave convex procedure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of semantic classes, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The datasets used in the paper involve different modalities, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the optimization procedure used in the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
